Recent Reviews
Afro Samurai: Resurrection Director's Cut DVD
To those seasoned on what to expect from a big Hollywood blockbuster, just like those noisy, expensive cinematic confections we flock to every summer, it's a whole lot of time, money and talent dumped into a pretty terrible script.
Bleach DVD 14
New powers are flaunted, old techniques dusted off, and pent-up tensions explode in a catharsis of violence. In other words: it's climax time.
Vampire Knight GN 5
Volume five dials down what little humor Hino had left in her nearly to zero…while dialing up the aesthetic distress of the series' signature love triangle.
The Story of Saiunkoku Season 1 Part 2 DVD
Intricate scheming, politicking, power plays, and prospective romance are the norm as this rescued Geneon title delivers twelve more episodes of delightful entertainment. Despite its heavy shojo trappings, this series deserves a broader audience than it will probably ever get.
Ral Ω Grad GN 3
Ral pretty much has a full RPG party now—but if this is how the series is transitioning into the main storyline, it doesn't inspire a whole lot of confidence.
Negima!? DVD Season 2 Part 1
There is more separating Negima!? and Negima! than just a question mark. Though billed as Season 2, Negima!? isn't a sequel so much as it is a complete re-imagining.
Fushigi Yûgi -VIZBIG Edition- GN 1
If you have not yet read Fushigi Yûgi, now is the perfect time to explore the Universe of the Four Gods. And even if you have already been there and back, you may discover that VIZ Media's new 3-in-1 omnibus edition is compelling enough an invitation for a nostalgic return trip.
Devil May Cry DVD 3
It's no coincidence that this volume features more extras for the Devil May Cry 4 game than for the series proper. After all, the game is the only thing the series has going for it.
Kujibiki Unbalance GN 2
Weak storytelling that's too straight-up to enjoy as parody and too clichéd to enjoy straight-up.
07-Ghost GN 1
Take a close look at the cover of the first volume of 07-Ghost. Needless to say, it is sublime truth in advertising, and if the illustration doesn't leave you drooling like a St. Bernard for more, don't bother with this manga for another second.
